<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="faq-header">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion">

      <!-- Auto-generated from user's questions -->
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q1">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a1">Common Questions about vaccination?</button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a1" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Below are some of the most common questions related to child immunization and vaccination practices in India.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q2">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a2">
            How do vaccines protect children from disease-causing organisms?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Vaccines activate the body’s immune response by generating antibodies against specific pathogens. These antibodies then protect children from real infections in the future.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q3">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a3">
            At what age should immunization start for any child?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Immunization starts immediately after birth with vaccines like BCG, OPV, and Hep B. Other vaccines follow as per the National Immunization Schedule.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q4">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a4">
            How much does the vaccination cost?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            All vaccines under the government immunization program are provided free of cost, including syringes and supplements.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q5">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a5">
            Where should the parents take their children for vaccination?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Parents can visit government hospitals, PHCs, CHCs, dispensaries, sub-centres, and Anganwadi centres. ANMs also hold immunization sessions in communities.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q6">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a6">
            Which vaccines are better – private or government-provided?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a6" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Both are equally safe and effective. Government vaccines are free and sourced from approved, licensed manufacturers, just like private ones.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q7">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a7">
            Why do private providers offer vaccines not available in government programmes?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a7" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Government focuses on diseases with large public health impact. Private providers may offer additional vaccines upon individual request and payment.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q8">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a8">
            Since India is polio-free, why is the polio vaccine still given?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a8" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Polio still exists in other countries. To prevent reintroduction, polio vaccines are continued in routine and pulse campaigns until global eradication.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q9">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a9">
            Why is there pain and swelling at the injection site?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a9" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Mild redness, pain, or swelling is normal after injectable vaccines. It usually resolves within 1-3 days and is not a sign of a bad reaction.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q10">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a10">
            What causes fever after vaccination?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a10" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Mild fever, especially after Pentavalent or DPT, is a natural body reaction. It is self-limiting and subsides within a day or two.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q11">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a11">
            Can a sick child be vaccinated?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a11" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Yes, mild illness does not affect vaccination. Children with serious illness should wait until recovery before receiving vaccines.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q12">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a12">
            What if the vaccine is not available at the health facility?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a12" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            The child will be given available vaccines, and others will be administered at the next session or at a higher-level facility.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="q13">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#a13">
            Do OPV cause impotency or does MR vaccine cause autism?
          </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="a13" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            No. These are myths. All vaccines in the government program are safe, effective, and tested for quality. They do not cause impotency or autism.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

